### enum  {#ac7324b67d7e3be270177e6590f0bb1e5}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::ARMSubtarget::ARMLdStMultipleTiming ">
What kind of timing do load multiple/store multiple instructions have.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="ac7324b67d7e3be270177e6590f0bb1e5a97d6452d484864e16c59e4c1032af8dc" />
<EnumerationListItem name="DoubleIssue">
Can load/store 2 registers/cycle
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ac7324b67d7e3be270177e6590f0bb1e5a15d56a42a3f8569bb24a0cdc215d9729" />
<EnumerationListItem name="DoubleIssueCheckUnalignedAccess">
Can load/store 2 registers/cycle, but needs an extra cycle if the access is not 64-bit aligned
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ac7324b67d7e3be270177e6590f0bb1e5a4036c7f30f9ea851473b06416cbbc160" />
<EnumerationListItem name="SingleIssue">
Can load/store 1 register/cycle
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ac7324b67d7e3be270177e6590f0bb1e5aeeb858b21b645dd260c1c4b16ccb5e23" />
<EnumerationListItem name="SingleIssuePlusExtras">
Can load/store 1 register/cycle, but needs an extra cycle for address computation and potentially also for register writeback
</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

### enum  {#ab3f7c70dd539567001e35caea74ade4b}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::ARMSubtarget::PushPopSplitVariation ">
How the push and pop instructions of callee saved general-purpose registers should be split.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="ab3f7c70dd539567001e35caea74ade4bafba6217ab4616d2f03a247754157ed96" />
<EnumerationListItem name="NoSplit">
All GPRs can be pushed in a single instruction
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab3f7c70dd539567001e35caea74ade4ba5ba862e3a9b6eca2a66b539bd990761c" />
<EnumerationListItem name="SplitR7">
R7 and LR must be adjacent, because R7 is the frame pointer, and must point to a frame record consisting of the previous frame pointer and the return address
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab3f7c70dd539567001e35caea74ade4ba2fba6120097ea9615c4a13a82fe8042d" />
<EnumerationListItem name="SplitR11WindowsSEH">
When the stack frame size is not known (because of variable-sized objects or realignment), Windows SEH requires the callee-saved registers to be stored in three regions, with R11 and LR below the floating-point registers
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab3f7c70dd539567001e35caea74ade4ba79139b30a7b6a6caf15fe7c26898cb1c" />
<EnumerationListItem name="SplitR11AAPCSSignRA">
When generating AAPCS-compilant frame chains, R11 is the frame pointer, and must be pushed adjacent to the return address (LR)

### SupportsTailCall {#ae97e07d14d7e5aec61a9f299f9793036}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="bool llvm::ARMSubtarget::SupportsTailCall = false"
  labels = {["protected"]}>
